The Krupp family, including Gustav &amp; Bertha, was the subject of a 2009 miniseries on German TV, &quot;Krupp, a German Family.&quot;  

Von Bohlen was a diplomat before the Kaiser arranged that he marry Bertha and take control of the company (which celebrates its 200th anniversary in 2012).  <a href="http://www.deutsche-gesellschaft-fuer-ordenskunde.de/vereinsmagazin/hefte/pdf/ausgabe66.pdf" rel="nofollow">www.deutsche-gesellschaft-fuer-ordenskunde.de/vereinsmaga...</a> has an article (in German) that focuses on his many decorations and a piece of jewellery made of miniatures of the medals.  It includes a 1910 picture of him in the dress uniform of the &quot;Leib-
Garde-Husaren-Regiments&quot; -- Lifeguard Hussars.  This is probably the regimental headgear of the same regiment.
